# Environment Variables Setup

Add these to your `.env.local` file in `packages/react-app`:

```bash
# ============================================
# Gasless x402 Configuration
# ============================================

# Server wallet private key (pays gas for settlements)
# This wallet needs CELO for gas (~0.001 CELO per settlement)
SERVER_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# Earnbase agent wallet (receives USDC payments)
NEXT_PUBLIC_EARNBASE_AGENT_WALLET=0xF3a5E77DD4b4277c07591aB5dD6Fd15f98F6D3Fa

# USDC contract address (Celo Mainnet)
NEXT_PUBLIC_USDC_ADDRESS=0xcebA9300f2b948710d2653dD7B07f33A8B32118C

# Celo RPC URL
CELO_RPC_URL=https://forno.celo.org

# ============================================
# Existing Configuration
# ============================================

# WalletConnect Project ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_WC_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id

# Database URL
DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
```

## Important Notes

1. **SERVER_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY**: This is a NEW wallet specifically for paying gas on behalf of agents. Keep it secure!

2. **Funding Requirements**:
   - Server wallet needs: **0.1 CELO** (for gas)
   - Agent wallet needs: **USDC** (for receiving payments)

3. **Security**:
   - Never commit `.env.local` to git
   - Use different wallets for server and agent
   - Monitor server wallet balance

## Quick Setup

```bash
# 1. Copy this file
cp .env.example .env.local

# 2. Generate a new server wallet (or use existing)
# You can use any wallet tool to generate a private key

# 3. Fund the server wallet with CELO
# Send 0.1 CELO to the server wallet address

# 4. Update the values in .env.local

# 5. Restart your dev server
npm run dev
```
